        <item>
            <title>0.3.540</title>
            <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:47:00 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>540</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.540</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.540</h2>
<p class="sub">Fixes duplicated bikes after an iCloud re-sync.</p>

<h3>Fixed: bikes showing twice</h3>
<ul>
  <li>After certain iCloud re-syncs, every bike could appear <b>twice</b>, with
  its rides split across the two copies. ChainLink already auto-healed
  duplicated rides and profiles this way, but bikes had no such pass — now they
  do. On launch it merges any duplicate bike back into one (matched by its
  stable identifier, so genuinely different bikes are never combined), moving
  <b>every ride, part, and maintenance record</b> onto the surviving bike. No
  data is lost, and it settles itself the next time you open the app.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
